42:37.973 --> 42:41.226
- Hi.
- All right...

42:41.309 --> 42:42.852
- There you go.
- Thanks.

42:42.936 --> 42:44.646
Yeah, I can get you more
if you need, all right?

42:44.729 --> 42:46.022
- What's up, Farhad?
- What's up, man?

42:46.106 --> 42:48.024
- This is Farhad.
- Don't-care-had.

42:48.108 --> 42:50.819
Nice to meet you.
And I'm going home.

42:50.902 --> 42:51.945
All right,
I'll see you later.

42:52.028 --> 42:53.822
- Thanks, Debs.
- See you guys.

43:00.537 --> 43:02.539
Huh.

43:02.622 --> 43:04.457
So what do you think?

43:04.541 --> 43:06.042
I mean, this could work, right?

43:06.876 --> 43:08.044
You know, when you
said basement,

43:08.128 --> 43:10.338
I was like, "The only people
who live in basements

43:10.422 --> 43:13.049
are serial killers
or 14-year-olds."

43:13.133 --> 43:15.093
This is way worse.

43:15.176 --> 43:17.053
Smells like something
died down here.

43:17.137 --> 43:19.222
Oh, yeah.
Lots of things died down here.

43:20.599 --> 43:22.851
Were they babies?

43:25.186 --> 43:26.438
No. Dogs.

43:26.521 --> 43:28.064
Ah.

43:28.148 --> 43:30.108
Was this also
a homeless encampment?

43:30.191 --> 43:31.192
Kinda.

43:31.276 --> 43:33.987
Okay, was <i>Silence of the Lambs</i>
filmed down here?

43:34.070 --> 43:35.572
I mean, where's the pit?

43:35.655 --> 43:36.740
You know, it's actually
out back.

43:36.823 --> 43:38.241
Come on, I'll show you.

43:38.325 --> 43:39.576
Come on.

43:42.829 --> 43:44.456
Finally.

43:45.206 --> 43:48.835
The chance to have
what everyone else has.

43:48.918 --> 43:50.420
Children.

43:52.213 --> 43:53.923
You've given me that, Frank.

43:54.007 --> 43:56.885
I don't know that I can
ever thank you enough.

43:56.968 --> 43:58.470
Should we say a little prayer?

44:00.972 --> 44:02.515
That's a great idea.

44:02.599 --> 44:04.643
I'll do it,
since I was Catholic.

44:06.061 --> 44:07.687
Mm.

44:08.938 --> 44:10.815
Heavenly Father,

44:10.899 --> 44:12.859
sweet Mary,

44:12.942 --> 44:16.154
that donkey,
little drummer boy,

44:16.237 --> 44:18.782
as my swimmers swim
through the valley

44:18.865 --> 44:21.368
of the shadow of death,
may they fear no evil.

44:21.451 --> 44:23.703
May my rod and my staff

44:23.787 --> 44:25.372
have power and glory

44:25.455 --> 44:28.750
forever and ever,
amen.

44:28.833 --> 44:30.669
- Amen.
- Amen.

44:30.752 --> 44:32.128
That was beautiful.

44:33.171 --> 44:34.172
Hello, Doctor.

44:34.255 --> 44:35.674
Frank, Ingrid.

44:35.757 --> 44:37.425
How are we looking?

44:39.094 --> 44:40.387
It's a miracle.

44:40.470 --> 44:42.722
Your motility
and concentration scores

44:42.806 --> 44:43.890
are through the roof.

44:43.973 --> 44:45.350
Whoo-hoo!

44:45.433 --> 44:46.851
Some of the highest
I've ever seen.

44:46.935 --> 44:48.895
Yeah. So...

44:48.978 --> 44:50.355
my boys can swim, eh?

44:50.438 --> 44:51.731
Swim?

44:51.815 --> 44:53.191
Whoa.

44:53.274 --> 44:54.859
Hello, laddies.

44:54.943 --> 44:56.945
Half of them tried to leap
out of the Petri dish.

44:57.028 --> 44:58.279
That's my boys.

44:58.363 --> 45:01.032
So, uh, you think
our chances are good?

45:01.116 --> 45:02.117
I'm extremely optimistic.

45:02.200 --> 45:03.201
Whew.

45:03.284 --> 45:04.202
Thank you.

45:04.285 --> 45:05.829
That's amazing.

45:05.912 --> 45:07.455
Th-thank you,
Dr. Kwan.

45:07.539 --> 45:09.290
Don't thank me.
Thank Frank.

45:10.166 --> 45:12.794
Frank, thank you.

45:14.838 --> 45:16.047
- Thank you.
- You bet.

45:16.131 --> 45:17.924
Thank you.

45:18.007 --> 45:19.634
You guys have got
to start living like grown-ups,

45:19.718 --> 45:21.678
and that starts
in the bathroom.

45:21.761 --> 45:23.138
All right.

45:23.221 --> 45:24.848
Okay. All right.

45:24.931 --> 45:27.809
Okay, okay, okay.

45:28.935 --> 45:30.311
So you've got, uh,

45:30.395 --> 45:32.814
a bottle of dishwashing liquid
in the shower

45:32.897 --> 45:34.482
and a bar of soap
with five different colors

45:34.566 --> 45:35.984
of pubes on it.

45:36.067 --> 45:38.236
Wait, you guys can't all
share one bar of soap.

45:38.319 --> 45:39.612
No, no, I don't.

45:39.696 --> 45:41.239
That's why I have
the dishwashing liquid.

45:41.322 --> 45:42.741
Is that why you always
smell like lemons?

45:42.824 --> 45:44.242
Yeah, I like lemons.

45:45.410 --> 45:46.411
Once you're in your 20s,

45:46.494 --> 45:49.205
you should have at least two
bath towels that match.

45:49.289 --> 45:50.874
Now that I'm in my 20s,
I'm just glad

45:50.957 --> 45:52.125
I'm not in fucking jail.

45:52.208 --> 45:54.961
Fair.

45:55.044 --> 45:56.045
Cheers.

45:56.129 --> 45:57.964
- Thanks.
- Thanks.

45:59.132 --> 46:00.592
Oh, uh, miss?

46:00.675 --> 46:01.676
Hi.

46:01.760 --> 46:03.386
Um, I asked for no dressing.

46:04.137 --> 46:06.556
- You sure?
- Yeah, positive.

46:06.639 --> 46:08.099
Yeah, this dressing
contains mayonnaise,

46:08.183 --> 46:09.392
and I'm allergic to eggs.

46:09.476 --> 46:11.352
I'm allergic to people
with allergies.

46:11.436 --> 46:12.771
You don't hear me whining.

46:13.938 --> 46:15.356
Excuse me?

46:15.440 --> 46:17.776
I'd like to speak
to the manager.

46:17.859 --> 46:18.860
Okay.

46:21.488 --> 46:22.739
Hi.

46:22.822 --> 46:23.823
You wanted to speak
to the manager?

46:23.907 --> 46:25.074
What seems to be the problem?

46:25.575 --> 46:27.035
- You're the manager?
- Mm-hmm.

46:27.118 --> 46:30.121
- Well, you're rude.
- Okay.

46:30.205 --> 46:32.540
- Oh, no, are you leaving?
- Yeah.

46:32.624 --> 46:34.083
And I'm never coming back.

46:34.167 --> 46:35.794
Okay, 'cause what
I could really use

46:35.877 --> 46:38.379
are some more customers
who are allergic to food.

46:38.463 --> 46:39.923
Bye.

46:42.967 --> 46:44.302
This is alive.

46:44.385 --> 46:45.970
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.
Let me see.

46:47.055 --> 46:49.432
- What are you doing?
- Sterilizing it.

46:49.516 --> 46:51.059
Just a minute.
Kills the bacteria.

46:51.142 --> 46:53.144
No, you guys.
That's a myth.

46:53.228 --> 46:54.938
It actually creates
super bacteria,

46:55.021 --> 46:56.606
which is even more dangerous.

46:56.689 --> 46:57.774
Oh, you see, we're a bit
more worried about

46:57.857 --> 46:59.692
super-tweaky
meth freaks, so...

46:59.776 --> 47:01.194
Okay, well,
sponges are, like,

47:01.277 --> 47:03.154
five for a dollar,
so you shouldn't have

47:03.238 --> 47:04.405
a maintenance plan
for your sponge.

47:04.489 --> 47:06.115
When it gets dirty,
just throw it away.

47:06.199 --> 47:07.659
Gotcha.

47:07.742 --> 47:09.536
Do you guys reuse your Q-tips?

47:09.619 --> 47:10.703
No, don't answer that.

47:10.787 --> 47:12.956
Also, there's one more thing.

47:14.916 --> 47:16.668
- What is this?
- It's a box of clean underwear.

47:16.751 --> 47:17.961
Yeah, we share our underwear.

47:18.044 --> 47:19.128
I don't have time to fold.
Do you, Debs?

47:19.212 --> 47:21.089
- Nope.
- Oh.

47:21.172 --> 47:22.298
Okay.

47:22.382 --> 47:24.926
All right, I'm a little
surprised I have to say this,

47:25.009 --> 47:28.221
but you guys should each have
your own underwear.

47:28.304 --> 47:29.347
Why do you give a shit?

47:29.430 --> 47:30.515
No one's asking you
to stay here.

47:30.598 --> 47:31.599
You can go.

47:31.683 --> 47:32.684
We had a mom once.

47:32.767 --> 47:33.935
She didn't stick around.

47:34.018 --> 47:35.311
Okay, sorry.

47:35.395 --> 47:36.855
I was just making a suggestion.

47:36.938 --> 47:38.147
So was I.

47:38.231 --> 47:40.859
Hey, I thought I was
the angry one.

47:40.942 --> 47:43.278
- What are you doing?
- Vampire power.

47:43.361 --> 47:45.655
Appliances use electricity
just from being plugged in.

47:45.738 --> 47:46.990
So that's why I'm
going to make sure

47:47.073 --> 47:49.075
shit stays unplugged
from now on.

47:49.158 --> 47:50.201
- That's smart.
- Whoa, watch out.

47:50.285 --> 47:52.161
- Whoa, Jesus.
- What's up?

47:52.245 --> 47:54.330
- Hi.
- Here.

47:54.414 --> 47:57.125
- Where'd you get this from?
- Yeah, I won a bet.

47:59.919 --> 48:01.546
God, you guys, seriously.

48:01.629 --> 48:03.756
We do not need this fan
plugged in.

48:03.840 --> 48:05.383
I could fly a fucking kite
in here.

48:06.092 --> 48:07.427
What...

48:07.510 --> 48:08.928
what the hell is going on?

48:09.012 --> 48:10.597
So for every one of these
we recharge,

48:10.680 --> 48:11.931
we make, like, 15 bucks.

48:12.015 --> 48:13.182
So we're gonna go out
every single day,

48:13.266 --> 48:14.017
collect 'em,
and recharge 'em.

48:14.100 --> 48:15.018
Mm-hmm.

48:15.101 --> 48:16.394
- Carl.
- What?

48:16.477 --> 48:18.396
I just paid an $800
electric bill.

48:18.479 --> 48:20.315
You cannot be charging
scooters in here.

48:20.398 --> 48:21.733
Power's not free.

48:21.816 --> 48:23.651
I'm not using our power.

48:25.820 --> 48:28.865
<i>♪♪ Got your mind on a mission ♪♪</i>

48:28.948 --> 48:31.659
<i>♪♪ A sick city vision ♪♪</i>

48:31.743 --> 48:35.705
<i>♪♪ The sun and moon
are kissing for you ♪♪</i>

48:35.788 --> 48:37.582
<i>♪♪ Hey... ♪♪</i>

48:37.665 --> 48:40.001
Just so you know,
this is considered stealing.

48:40.084 --> 48:42.045
Hey, just so you know,
the people that live here

48:42.128 --> 48:43.880
have a sign
in their front yard that says

48:43.963 --> 48:45.548
"Drive like your kids
live here."

48:45.632 --> 48:47.634
Plug that fucker in.

48:47.717 --> 48:50.470
<i>♪♪ Hey, gotta get down,
gotta shake it to the ground ♪♪</i>

48:50.553 --> 48:53.723
<i>♪♪ I'm a runaround ♪♪</i>

48:59.729 --> 49:03.191
All right, turn this
into more drinks, please.

49:03.274 --> 49:05.360
Evening, dream team.

49:05.443 --> 49:07.528
Can I get a...

49:07.612 --> 49:09.739
a beer and a bump?

49:12.533 --> 49:15.453
- What?
- That's my stool.

49:17.664 --> 49:19.248
Well, tough shit.
Looks like it's my stool now.

49:19.332 --> 49:20.959
Come on, it's my stool.
That's where I sit.

49:21.042 --> 49:22.794
Come on, let me sit here.

49:22.877 --> 49:25.838
Get--fuck.
All right, fine. Jesus.

49:28.299 --> 49:29.676
Who's the new barback?

49:29.759 --> 49:30.760
That's Santiago.

49:30.843 --> 49:32.804
He's staying with us
until we find his father.

49:32.887 --> 49:34.097
Wh-where'd he come from?

49:34.180 --> 49:35.682
What we thought
was Child Services.

49:35.765 --> 49:38.476
Santiago said that there are
1,000 boys living there.

49:39.060 --> 49:41.020
Got separated
from their families.

49:41.104 --> 49:42.689
Crying, sleeping on the floor.

49:42.772 --> 49:44.440
Wearing tinfoil blankets.

49:44.524 --> 49:46.609
- What the fuck?
- It's like the Trail of Tears.

49:46.693 --> 49:48.403
I don't remember exactly
what that was,

49:48.486 --> 49:50.279
but they wouldn't call it that
if they weren't crying.

49:50.363 --> 49:51.948
Well, they are here
illegally.

49:52.031 --> 49:53.700
They were
escaping violence.

49:53.783 --> 49:56.452
They came to Chicago
to escape violence?

49:56.536 --> 49:58.246
I don't see what
the big deal is.

49:58.329 --> 50:00.081
They got some hot meals,
somewhere to sleep.

50:00.164 --> 50:01.874
It's kind of like
a summer camp for them.

50:01.958 --> 50:03.501
It's gotta be better
than where they came from.

50:03.584 --> 50:06.045
Yeah, Tommy, it's a regular
fucking country club.

50:06.129 --> 50:07.672
What are you doing?

50:07.755 --> 50:09.173
I am not with you on this.

50:11.676 --> 50:14.429
They got separated
from their parents.

50:14.512 --> 50:16.889
You know, their lives
were so shitty

50:16.973 --> 50:19.350
that they risked everything
to come to this country,

50:19.434 --> 50:20.893
of all places.

50:20.977 --> 50:23.062
Yeah, land of the free.

50:23.146 --> 50:24.689
Home of the brave.

50:24.772 --> 50:26.899
Yeah, at least the brave part
is still true.

50:26.983 --> 50:28.651
<i>- ♪♪ Oh, say... ♪♪</i>
- No, no.

50:28.735 --> 50:30.695
<i>Silencio. Por favor.</i>

50:30.778 --> 50:32.155
<i>Silencio.</i>

50:35.241 --> 50:36.826
Can I buy you a drink?

50:37.201 --> 50:38.202
Yes.

50:38.286 --> 50:39.620
Hey, pump the brakes,
cool breeze.

50:39.704 --> 50:40.913
- She's had enough.
- What?

50:40.997 --> 50:42.582
Let the guy buy me a drink

50:42.665 --> 50:44.584
if he wants to buy a girl
a drink.

50:44.667 --> 50:46.836
Two rum and diets, please.

50:48.546 --> 50:51.049
- Do you wanna...party?
- Sure.

50:51.132 --> 50:52.133
No.

50:52.216 --> 50:53.634
Nope, no, no.

50:53.718 --> 50:54.677
Nope.

50:54.761 --> 50:56.054
Nope, nope, no.

50:56.137 --> 50:57.722
Come on.

50:58.181 --> 50:59.348
- What'd I do?
- I don't like you.

50:59.432 --> 51:01.017
But I dropped something.

51:06.814 --> 51:08.566
What the fuck is that?

51:08.649 --> 51:10.068
What? What?

51:10.151 --> 51:11.360
That scratching noise.

51:13.488 --> 51:15.490
I don't hear anything.

51:15.573 --> 51:17.533
Something is crawling around
inside your walls.

51:17.617 --> 51:21.120
It's probably rats
the size of toasters.

51:21.204 --> 51:22.371
There, that.

51:22.455 --> 51:23.873
There it is again.

51:28.169 --> 51:29.378
There.

51:29.462 --> 51:31.005
Fixed it.

51:32.548 --> 51:33.800
<i>Hey, Gallaghers.</i>

51:33.883 --> 51:36.052
<i>Got a present for ya.</i>

51:36.135 --> 51:38.221
Now what?

51:44.102 --> 51:45.770
Shit.

51:45.853 --> 51:47.730
Jesus.

51:48.189 --> 51:50.274
She's fine.
Just passed out.

51:50.358 --> 51:51.901
Sweet dreams, baby girl.

51:51.984 --> 51:53.694
Well, she's all yours.

51:53.778 --> 51:55.154
We gotta get back to the bar.

51:55.238 --> 51:57.323
- Thanks, guys.
- Thanks.

51:57.406 --> 51:59.784
She do this a lot?

51:59.867 --> 52:00.993
Yeah.

52:01.077 --> 52:02.495
Well, lately.

